Add (or update) this file at the repository root. It documents every variable you’ll need, including the new
spam‑protection ones.

# ---------------- SMTP Configuration ----------------
SMTP_HOST=                # e.g. smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587             # 587 for STARTTLS, 465 for SSL
SMTP_SECURE=false         # true for port 465, false for 587 (STARTTLS)
SMTP_USER=                # username or “apikey” for services like SendGrid
SMTP_PASS=                # password or API key
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Ezri Daniel Gweth
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=ezridgweth@gweenscraft.co.ke
CONTACT_RECIPIENT=ezridgweth@gweenscraft.co.ke   # where you want to receive the mail

# ---------------- Spam‑protection Settings ----------------
# How many requests are allowed per IP within the window below?
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=5
# Window in seconds (e.g. 60 = per minute)
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=60

Never commit the real .env – it contains your credentials.
Keep .env listed in .gitignore (your repo already has it)..